@startuml
title IPsec Processing Databases and the Security Association
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #FDEEEE
  BorderColor #B54A4A
}
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #B54A4A
}

database "SPD\nSecurity Policy\nDatabase" as SPD
database "SAD\nSecurity Association\nDatabase" as SAD
database "PAD\nPeer Authorization\nDatabase\n(IPsec-v3)" as PAD

[Outbound / inbound\npacket] as PKT
[IKE\n(key management)] as IKE

PKT --> SPD : match selectors
SPD --> SAD : discard / bypass / protect\n-> find SA
SAD --> PKT : apply SA\n(SPI, algorithms, keys)
IKE --> SAD : install negotiated SA
IKE --> PAD : consult for\npeer authentication
PAD ..> IKE : authorizes peer

note right of SAD
  An SA is one-way and named by
  its SPI; a two-way flow needs a pair.
  Mode: transport or tunnel.
end note
@enduml
